"How Not to Play 'There Is No Game' 🙅‍♂️🕹️

Attempting to play 'There Is No Game' may sound counterintuitive, but if you insist on not playing it the right way, here are some anti-tips for you:

Ignore Your Mouse: Even though there are no instructions in a game that doesn't exist, try using your mouse anyway. It might not help, but who knows? Maybe the nonexistent game will respond to your futile attempts.

Mute is the Way to Go: Turn off the sound. The narrator may try to drop hints, but who needs that, right? Progressing without any auditory clues is the key to not getting anywhere in 'There Is No Game.'

Avoid Unusual Things: If you find something slightly askew or out of the ordinary, ignore it completely. It won't assist you in progressing through the game. After all, how can you progress in a game that claims not to exist?
